---

<Base
  title={title}
  description={metaDescription}
  canonical={canonical}
>
  <script slot="schema" type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(localBusinessSchema)} />
  <script slot="schema" type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(serviceSchema)} />

  <Header slot="header" />

  <div class="container py-6">
    <Breadcrumbs
      items={[
        { label: "Kitchen Fitter Solihull", href: "/kitchen-fitter-solihull/" },
      ]}
    />
  </div>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="section" style="background: var(--bg-light);">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold mb-5 leading-tight" style="color: var(--navy);">
          Kitchen Fitter Solihull — Independent Kitchen Installation by Pindi Sahota
        </h1>
        <AnswerBlock
          answer="Pindi Sahota is an independent kitchen fitter serving Solihull, West Midlands, covering B91, B92 and B93. With 30 years of experience fitting large, premium kitchens across Solihull's affluent housing stock — from Solihull town and Knowle to Dorridge and Dickens Heath — he delivers a fixed-price quote after a £195 pre-installation survey, credited back in full on booking."
        />
        <KeyTakeaway points={takeawayPoints} />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Photo Gallery -->
  <section class="section gallery-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6" style="color: var(--navy);">Kitchen Installations in Solihull</h2>
      <div class="gallery-grid">
        <figure class="gallery-item">
          <img
            src="/assets/kitchen-fitter/kitchen-fitter-solihull-grey-handleless-kitchen-west-midlands-3024x4032.webp"
            alt="Kitchen fitter Solihull — grey handleless kitchen installation in Solihull, West Midlands by Install My Kitchen"
            width="3024"
            height="4032"
            loading="lazy"
            class="gallery-img"
          />
          <figcaption class="gallery-caption">Grey handleless kitchen — Solihull, West Midlands</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="gallery-item">
          <img
            src="/assets/kitchen-fitter/kitchen-fitter-solihull-navy-kitchen-island-installation-3024x4032.webp"
            alt="Kitchen fitter Solihull — navy blue kitchen with island fitted in Solihull, West Midlands"
            width="3024"
            height="4032"
            loading="lazy"
            class="gallery-img"
          />
          <figcaption class="gallery-caption">Navy blue kitchen with island — Solihull, West Midlands</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="gallery-item">
          <img
            src="/assets/kitchen-fitter/kitchen-fitter-solihull-white-handleless-black-granite-worktop-2448x3264.webp"
            alt="Kitchen fitter Solihull — white handleless kitchen with black granite worktop installed in Solihull B91"
            width="2448"
            height="3264"
            loading="lazy"
            class="gallery-img"
          />
          <figcaption class="gallery-caption">White handleless kitchen with black granite worktop — Solihull B91</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 1: Independent vs Retailer Fitters -->
  <section class="section" style="background: var(--bg-light);">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-3xl fade-up">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--navy);">
          Why Independent Kitchen Fitting Matters in Solihull
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Solihull homeowners typically invest significantly in their kitchens — and for good reason. The housing stock demands it. A large 1930s detached home in Solihull town, a period property in Knowle, or an executive new-build in Cheswick Green will often accommodate a kitchen of 20 or more units, a central island, and a full suite of integrated appliances. When the kitchen itself costs £10,000 or more, the fitting choice matters enormously.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Retailer-provided fitting schemes — offered as an add-on by Wren, Magnet, and others — use contractor networks where individual fitters are paid to move quickly and meet targets, not to spend an additional hour ensuring a worktop joint is invisible or that an island is perfectly level. Because they work for the retailer, their accountability runs to the retailer's cost model first.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          An independent kitchen fitter like Pindi Sahota works directly for you, not for any retailer. He visits your home before the project begins, builds a fixed-price quote based on the actual conditions in your kitchen, and carries out all the work himself. There is no handover between a planner, a coordinator, and an unknown fitter. The person who surveys the job is the person who fits it.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          For a Solihull kitchen — where the specification is high, the rooms are large, and the homeowner's expectations are correspondingly elevated — independent fitting is the right choice.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 2: Solihull Housing Stock -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-3xl fade-up">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--navy);">
          Solihull's Housing Stock — What Pindi Knows
        </h2>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Solihull's reputation as one of the most prosperous towns in the West Midlands is built on a genuinely varied and high-quality housing stock. Understanding the differences across the town's neighbourhoods is part of what makes a skilled, experienced fitter indispensable.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          In Solihull town itself — the area around the station, Touchwood, and Malvern Park — the dominant property type is the large 1930s and 1940s detached and semi-detached home. These are often described locally as the "Solihull semi", a misnomer: they are typically four- or five-bedroom homes with wide rear extensions, generous kitchen footprints, and original features such as quarry-tile floors, chimney breasts, and solid external walls of nine-inch brick. Levelling and setting out in these rooms requires care and experience.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Knowle and Dorridge, further south into B93, are characterised by post-war executive detached homes on substantial plots, many extended and renovated over the decades. Kitchens here are often the result of combining two original rooms or removing a chimney stack — which means irregular shapes, varying ceiling heights, and unusual wall angles that must be accounted for during both design and fitting.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Dickens Heath and Cheswick Green represent Solihull's newer residential development — mostly built from the 1990s onward, with contemporary open-plan kitchen-diners designed around island layouts, bifold doors, and integrated appliance banks. These kitchens are technically straightforward but demand precision at every stage to deliver the clean, seamless finish the design intends.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Pindi has worked across all of these property types, across B91, B92, and B93. That accumulated experience — knowing what to look for, what to plan around, and how to solve problems on the day — is what a 30-year independent career produces.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 3: The Survey-First Process -->
  <section class="section" style="background: var(--bg-light);">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-3xl fade-up">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--navy);">
          The Survey-First Process — How It Works in Solihull
        </h2>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Every kitchen fitting project begins with a pre-installation survey carried out by Pindi personally. The survey costs £195 and is credited back in full if you proceed with the installation. It is not a sales visit — it is a working appointment that produces a detailed, accurate quote based on the real conditions of your home.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          During the survey, Pindi takes precise room measurements, checks ceiling heights and wall angles, inspects existing plumbing and electrics routes, reviews your kitchen plan and elevation drawings, and identifies any preparatory work required before installation day — floor levelling, plastering, electrics, gas work, or tiling. In Solihull's older homes, in particular, these checks are essential: an apparently straightforward kitchen installation in a 1930s semi can involve levelling across a 30mm drop or scribing around a chimney breast that was not on the original plan.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          After the survey you receive a written, fixed-price quote. The price does not change unless you change the scope of the work. There are no retrospective charges for complications that should have been identified in advance.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Survey appointments in Solihull are typically available within two weeks. Installation slots follow within four to eight weeks of the survey. To book, call <a href="tel:07399651836" class="font-semibold" style="color: var(--teal);">07399 651836</a> or visit the <a href="/survey/" class="font-semibold" style="color: var(--teal);">survey booking page</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 4: Retailers -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-3xl fade-up">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--navy);">
          Which Kitchen Retailers Does Pindi Fit in Solihull?
        </h2>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Because Pindi is fully independent, he can fit kitchens purchased from any retailer or manufacturer. The most common kitchens he installs in Solihull include:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 mb-6 pl-1" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="mt-1 flex-shrink-0 w-5 h-5 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center" style="background: var(--teal); color: white; font-size: 0.65rem;">✓</span>
            <span><strong>Magnet</strong> — including the Belgravia painted shaker range, which suits Solihull's period homes particularly well. Pindi has fitted a Magnet Belgravia kitchen in Solihull with granite worktops and range cooker co-ordination. See the <a href="/retailers/magnet/" style="color: var(--teal);">Magnet installation page</a>.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="mt-1 flex-shrink-0 w-5 h-5 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center" style="background: var(--teal); color: white; font-size: 0.65rem;">✓</span>
            <span><strong>Wren Kitchens</strong> — one of the most widely purchased in Solihull; Pindi fits Wren independently without being tied to their installation scheme. See the <a href="/retailers/wren/" style="color: var(--teal);">Wren installation page</a>.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="mt-1 flex-shrink-0 w-5 h-5 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center" style="background: var(--teal); color: white; font-size: 0.65rem;">✓</span>
            <span><strong>Howdens Joinery</strong> — Pindi holds a trade account with Howdens, giving him direct depot access. The Greenwich and Tewkesbury collections are popular choices in Solihull's larger homes.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="mt-1 flex-shrink-0 w-5 h-5 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center" style="background: var(--teal); color: white; font-size: 0.65rem;">✓</span>
            <span><strong>Premium and German brands</strong> — Häcker, Nobilia, Mereway, Masterclass, Neptune, and deVOL are regularly fitted in Knowle, Dorridge, and the larger detached homes across B93.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="mt-1 flex-shrink-0 w-5 h-5 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center" style="background: var(--teal); color: white; font-size: 0.65rem;">✓</span>
            <span><strong>IKEA, Wickes, B&Q and Benchmarx</strong> — all covered as standard, with the same attention to detail regardless of the kitchen's price point.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          If your kitchen brand is not listed, call <a href="tel:07399651836" class="font-semibold" style="color: var(--teal);">07399 651836</a> — in almost every case it can be accommodated.
        </p>
